<F P=106> [By UKRINFORM correspondent Viktor Kovalenko -- TASS] </F>
  [Text] Kiev May 27 TASS -- Ukrainian parliament Chairman 
Aleksandr Moroz told a parliament session on Thursday that 
President Leonid Kravchuk intended to address lawmakers next 
Tuesday [31 May] in order to propose his solution of the Crimean 
problems. With this in view, the session decided to hold a 
closed-door plenary meeting on Tuesday morning. 
  The speaker also announced the Ukrainian president's 
intention to present for parliament's consideration his nominees 
for the post of prime minister. 
  Exercising his right to legislative initiatives, Kravchuk 
also plans to propose some amendments to the election law, Moroz 
said. 

